> The Meatball Minestrone for Lunch nutrition information is as follows: Calories: 370, Fat: 22 g, Saturated Fat: 5 g, Carbohydrate: 28 g, Sugar: 3 g, Fiber: 7 g, Protein: 31 g, Cholesterol: 150 mg, Sodium: 1960 mg.

> The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Chicken Sausage Meatball Dinner.

== Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Halve and peel
@Yellow Onion{1}; small-dice one half and thinly slice the other. Trim and
thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and halve
@Carrots{2} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch pieces. Halve, core, and
thinly slice @Apple{1}. Pick 1 tsp @Thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; leave
remaining sprigs whole.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 1 inch.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to
pot; mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}
and 1 TBSP @Butter{3%tablespoon}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cover and
keep warm until ready to serve.

== Meatballs ==

Using your hands, form @Italian Chicken Sausage{18%ounce} into small meatballs
(about 16). (TIP: To prevent the meat from sticking to your hands, lightly
dampen them with water.) Place meatballs on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.
Bake until browned and cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

== Cabbage and Collard Greens ==

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{6%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and whole thyme sprigs and cook, stirring,
until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, apple, and
another drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until
softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, half the scallion
greens, and @Sugar{½%teaspoon} (to taste); cook for ~{1%minute}. Discard thyme
sprigs. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Cover to keep warm.

== Minestrone ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add diced
onion, scallion whites, carrot, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Chicken Stock Concentrate{3}
and 3 cups water. Bring to a boil, then stir in @Cannellini Beans{13.4%ounce}
(and any liquid). Reduce heat to a simmer; season with salt and pepper. Stir in
half the meatballs; simmer ~{2%minutes}. Divide soup between 2 #reusable
containers{}. Divide @Spinach{5%ounce} between @plastic zip-close bags{}. When
ready to eat, stir spinach into soup. Microwave on high for ~{3-5%minutes},
or until heated through and spinach has wilted.

== Tuscan Herb Sauce ==

Rinse and wipe out pan used for cabbage. Melt 1 TBSP butter in same pan over
medium-high heat until melted. Stir in @Flour{1}; cook until lightly browned,
~{1-2%minutes}. Whisk in remaining @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and 1 cup
water. Cook until sauce is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Serve ==

Stir in another 1 TBSP butter and reserved 1 tsp thyme leaves. Divide mashed
potatoes and cabbage mixture between plates. Top mashed potatoes with remaining
meatballs and sauce. Garnish with remaining scallion greens.